      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# The character in the adventure is trying to distribute their weight so they can reach the top of the bridge ladder quicker. A program to help them achieve this consists of three functions as follows:\n",
        "# The first function should be named sum_weights and should have 2 parameters. The parameters represent the weight of the character and the weight of their inventory. The function should calculate and return the total weight.\n",
        "def sum_weights(character_weight, inventory_weight):\n",
        "    return character_weight + inventory_weight\n",
        "# The second function should be named calc_avg_weight and should also have 2 parameters. The parameters are the same as the previous function. The function should calculate and return the average weight of the items being weighed (person and inventory). It should do this by calling the first function and using the return value.\n",
        "def calc_avg_weight(character_weight, inventory_weight):\n",
        "    total_weight = sum_weights(character_weight, inventory_weight)\n",
        "    return total_weight / 2\n",
        "# The third function should be named run and should have 0 parameters. The function should prompt the user to enter the weight for the character and then their inventory. The function should then prompt the user to enter either the word \"sum\" or \"average\". If the user types in \"sum\" then this function should display the total weight as given by the first function ( sum_weights\"). Otherwise if the user types in \"average\" then this function should display the average weight as given by the second function ( calc_avg_weight).\n",
        "def run():\n",
        "    character_weight = float(input(\"Enter character weight: \"))\n",
        "    inventory_weight = float(input(\"Enter inventory weight: \"))\n",
        "    choice = input(\"Enter 'sum' or 'average': \")\n",
        "    if choice == \"sum\":\n",
        "        total_weight = sum_weights(character_weight, inventory_weight)\n",
        "        print(\"Total weight:\", total_weight)\n",
        "    else :\n",
        "        avg_weight = calc_avg_weight(character_weight, inventory_weight)\n",
        "        print(\"Average weight:\", avg_weight)s\n",
        "\n",
        "# The program should also contain a single call to your run function at the end of your program that looks as follows:\n",
        "run()"
      ],
